<Author>TravelingAggs
<Content>Great location...but that's it. The location for this hotel is great, and the price wasn't bad for an American Traveler; however, in the future I would spend the extra money to stay somewhere else.1. The business center was down the whole time we were there (3 days) so we couldn't use the free internet, which was a high selling point for us staying there.2. Our room was facing the main street (Via Laietana) and the noise overnight was terrible, even with earplugs. Lots of street traffic with thin windows.3. We had the do not disturb sign on our door, and came home one day to find they had entered our room, taken the third bed (we booked a double but they put us in a triple) and thrown our belongings around that had been placed on the extra bed. It was very disrespectful the way they handled our stuff. When I went to complain (which, I never have before) they were very unresponsive (and I speak Spanish). At the same time this was going on, an entire tour group from Boston had arrived two hours past check-in time and a lot of their rooms weren't ready.Location was great, actual rooms weren't bad, but the service and noise were enough to make me stay elsewhere on my next visit. 
