<Content>Great location, good price, just minor things .. It's a great location. Avoid the Olympic village area as it's cut off from the historic centre and the buzz. This is a great area. You could probably happily stay in a budget priced hotel on the same road. The hotel room sound proofing is excellent; the air conditioning too cold if anything!; good wi-fi; great breakfast; good restaurants nearby and can walk or metro almost anywhere. Rooms at the front get all the street noise so try to book the rear. Bath is quite small but shower fine. Minibar good for storing own snacks and drinks! A pool isn't that easy to find centrally so it's a bonus here. The hotel is just a bit unexciting but despite that I'd probably go back if I didn't find better in this area in this price range. Check prices against other websites as they can be better value than hotel directly. By the way, in the Barcelona restaurants generally watch out for the charge for the bread. 3 large slices of bread on a plate, with a thin coating of oil, presented without invitation, cost 鈧? - even if one slice only is consumed! 
