<Author>LJSWales
<Content>Hotel located in city centre, clean enjoyed the stay there. This hotel is located close to the city center, is clean and the staff are polite. This is a three star rating and is classed as a tourist hotel. There are a lot of them to choose from and I have stayed at others that were equally acceptable. Being close to the drop off point for the airport transfer bus was also handy, just a short walk from the main square.This is close to a large departmental store which has a basement supermarket which we found handy. The restaurant on top of this large departmental store is worth a visit, if you are lucky to get a window seat there is some view over the city and the food there is ok to.For touring the city I suggest you got to the main square (Plaza Catalunya) and buy tickets for the Red and Blue tourist buses. One goes North the other South and cover all of the main attractions. You are dropped off outside each attraction and when you are ready return to the drop off point as these buses are circulating all the time and the wait for the next bus is not long. Word of warning, I was there on one visit with my mother and a friend, my mother's hand bag was literally ripped off her shoulder snapping the trap, she was wearing it across her body and not just over her shoulder. Lucky for my mother I am athletic which was unlucky for the bag snatcher as after about 1/2 mile I caught up with him, lets just say I got the bag back. There is a lot to see in Barcelona and you will enjoy your time. If it is nice and sunny allow some time in parc g眉ell, there is plenty of seating there and you enjoy the relaxation and resting your feet ready for the next sight. A walk along Las Ramblas is a must, looking at all the Living Statues how they manage to stay so still for so long mystifies me and some of them are quite spectacular.Enjoy Barcelona, just take care with your possessions and what you carry and you will enjoy your visit. 
