<Author>WendsPaisley
<Content>Location, Location, Location ! Every other review refers to this - you can't beat the location of the Mont Blanc. It really is just 5 mins from the Placa Catalunya, where you get the airport bus for under 4euros, and 5 in the other direction to La Ramblas and the Gothic Quarter. Our room (802) had a balcony, complete with Astroturf (!), and was great to sit out on as the sun went down. My initial impression of the room was that it could do with redecoration but it was very clean and comfy and perfectly okay for a couple of nights stay. As we were celebrating 'significant birthdays', a friend had arranged for champers to be delivered and this arrived within minutes of checking in. I was really impressed with this as it had been arranged months in advance and could easily have been overlooked. We also got a voucher for a glass of Cava in the bar which was a nice touch. The hotel caters for both tourists and business purposes but never felt busy. The only time we saw any number of other guests was at breakfast, talking of which, was lovely and the waiting staff efficient. I wouldnt bother having dinner in the hotel as there are 101 places nearby including an Italian next door. I'd love to know if it was any good - it certainly looked so from the outside. This was my second time in Barcelona and it was as great as I remembered. Tons to see and do but if you're there for only a short time, take the bus tours as you'll see more than you ever could on foot. One thing I did notice to be different was fewer people begging (maybe the city fathers have tackled this issue) and it also felt very safe to walk about at night. The last time I was there, I was told off by a policeman for swinging my handbag about as we walked through the Place Reial (I'm a female reviewer by the way!) All in all, Barcelona is a great place for a short break and it's somewhere you could go back to time after time. And that goes for the Mont Blanc too! 
