<Content>Central location! Just back from a great week in Barcelona! We stayed in the Montblanc for one week. The hotel is in a central location - we got the aerobus from the airport (as recommended on this site) for 3 euro to placa de catalunya, walked down via fontanella and turned right down via laietana - only a few doors down. It saved us forking out a 30 euro taxi fare - nice not to get ripped off for once!In booking the hotel we found oh - barcelona to be a good website as it was possible to book our accommodation without the breakfast option (breakfast works out at 15 euro a head).At reception my boyfriend double-checked about our request for a double room as we checked in (we had read on some reviews that people had gotten two single beds pushed together, as opposed to a double bed). The receptionist quickly tore up the printout he was going to give us, and re-issued us with another room (another potentially annoying situation avoided!).The room was spacious (complete with double bed!) with a bright ensuite bathroom. The shower was really powerful. A hairdryer was also supplied - my only quip being that it is not strong enough to give a proper blow dry, so bring your own hairdryer plus adapter!. Our room was located on the first floor above the main hotel entrance on via laietana. My main gripe would be that via laietana is somewhat of a traffic corridor, and the traffic noise permeated the room constantly, but we got used to it. I had requested a room not on the street side in booking originally, (come to think of it I don't think the hotel had looked at one of our comments in the requests box!) but on the plus side our room was on the same level as the swimming pool which was nice as we didn't have to use the lift to get to it.The hotel location was really great - we were close to placa de catalunya to get the bus turistic and the little sidestreets on the right hand side were really bustling during the day with shoppers and full of restaurants at night time. These streets bring you onto Carrier d'Angel which has loads of shops Zara, Mango, El Corte Ingles etc. and will eventually bring you onto La Rambla.My main tourist advice would be not to eat on the Rambla full stop. Rip off central. There was an Irish pub across from the hotel called McCarthy's. They screen all the football and hurling games. The owner gave us some excellent recommendations of where to eat - Els Quatre Gats (The Four Cats) where Picasso went (40 -50 euro a head incl. wine) - a little bit on the pricey side but well worth it for a good meal and excellent ambiance. Milk also does good food (under Irish ownership) and La Rosa Negra which is a Mexican spot does an excellent lunch menu Menu del Dia priced at 8 euro per head for starter, main course and dessert plus drink on via laietana.I would stay in the Montblanc again and would recommend it to friends due to it's central location but I think that they need to be more aware of visitors' specific room requests, so check first when you are checking in!. 
