<Content>Great hotel We visited Barcelona in August 2004 as part of a party of six and were very pleasantly surprised by the Montblanc. After reading some mixed reviews on TripAdvisor, we were a little apprehensive, but left with a very positive opinion overall. The rooms seem to have been refurbished quite recently, and our rooms were at the rear of the hotel, overlooking the pool. It was very quiet and I'd recommend that any future guests ask for rooms at the rear with a pool view. The rooms themselves were of a very high standard which, in our opinion, exceeded that of a three-star place. The breakfast, which was part of our deal with Globespan, was excellent. The food was very fresh and there was a great choice of juices, yoghurts, cheeses, meats. fruits etc - the usual continental fare. In terms of location, the Montblanc is quite close to the marina and is about a five minute walk from the Barri Gotic and Las Ramblas. The only gripe we had was that the staff were a little snitty. However, we found in general that the people in the tourist business in Barcelona weren't as friendly as those we've encountered elsewhere in Spain.If I were to return to Barcelona, I'd stay at the Montblanc again - it's great value for money. 
